---
// Honest — known limitations the team chose to surface rather than hide.
---

<section id="honest" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--line);">
  <p class="eyebrow">
    <span class="num">08</span><span data-i18n="hon.eye">Honestly</span>
  </p>
  <h2 class="serif">
    <span data-i18n="hon.t1">Margin is still an</span>
    <em data-i18n="hon.t2">early MVP</em><span data-i18n="hon.t3">.</span>
  </h2>
  <p class="section-lede" data-i18n="hon.lede">
    It works well on article pages, legacy text-heavy pages, and a few
    high-value dynamic pages like X. But there are rough edges, and we're
    listing them here instead of hiding them.
  </p>

  <div class="features" style="background: var(--cream);">
    <div class="feature" style="padding-top: 28px;">
      <div class="num">L.01</div>
      <h3 data-i18n="lim.1t">Firefox isn't a primary target yet</h3>
      <p data-i18n="lim.1b">
        Chrome / Chromium first. Firefox will follow.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature" style="padding-top: 28px;">
      <div class="num">L.02</div>
      <h3 data-i18n="lim.2t">Some highly dynamic apps</h3>
      <p data-i18n="lim.2b">
        On SPAs that aggressively rewrite the DOM, translation blocks may get
        moved or removed. Working on it.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature" style="padding-top: 28px;">
      <div class="num">L.03</div>
      <h3 data-i18n="lim.3t">Large pages translate in batches</h3>
      <p data-i18n="lim.3b">
        To stay friendly with provider rate limits, translations appear
        progressively rather than all at once.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
